Thoughts.<br><br>
Jane apologized for her actions.  So what!  I don't care one way or the other.  She has to deal with and live with herself.  If her apology makes her feel better, so be it.  There came a point in my life where the &quot;mea culpas&quot; are fairly meaningless.  Robert McNamara had his &quot;mea culpa&quot; last year.<br><br>
We all (me) have felt remorse for some of our actions.  Who are the apologizes for?  I believe they are for us to relieve our guilts and senses of shame.  They are not primarily intended to the people that we have harmed.<br><br>
